step_data.thought: I've clicked on the 'Share' link and now I can see the sharing options are displayed. Looking at the accessibility tree, I can see elements related to sharing like 'Link or HTML' and a textbox with a URL. The URL in the textbox (element [318]) contains map coordinates but not the bounding box specifically. The URL format is 'http://openstreetmap.example.com/#map=6/42.900/-77.849' which shows the zoom level (6) and center coordinates (42.900, -77.849), but not the bounding box. Looking at the other options, I don't see explicit bounding box coordinates. I should check if there's an 'Export' option that might provide this information, as that's typically where bounding box coordinates would be available.
